    /photos/people/Doe_John/IMG_1234.HEIC
    ^^ all the same file!


DOS 3.3 DSK Filesystem
-----------------------

```
$ go run examples/dos33 DISK.DSK
Serving DOS 3.3 DSK filesystem over WebDAV
  Address: http://127.0.0.1:33333/dos33

# Mount to /Volumes/dos33
$ cd /Volumes/dos33/DISK.DSK
$ ls -1
README
files/
catalog
applesoft/
binary/
intbasic/
text/
a/
b/
r/
s/
locks/   # Might be unnecessary
vtoc

$ cat README
DOS 3.3 DSK Filesystem Folder Structure

files/      Read-only versions of all files, as raw binary
catalog     a close approximation of running CATLOG from DOS
locks/      All locked files. Lock a file by adding it; unlock by deleting it.

You can edit and create files by type under these folders:
  applesoft/
  intbasic/
  binary/
  text/
  a/
  b/
  r/
  s/

For the following "text" folders, the appropriate conversion takes place:
 applesoft/
 intbasic/
 text/

$ cat catalog

DISK VOLUME 254

 I 002 HELLO
*I 043 APPLESOFT
 I 016 ANIMALS
 I 009 COLOR DEMOS
*I 004 MASTER.CREATE
*B 039 RAWDOS
*I 007 COPY
*B 007 COPY.OBJ


$ ls -1 files/
HELLO
APPLESOFT
ANIMALS
COLOR DEMOS
MASTER.CREATE
RAWDOS
COPY
COPY.OBJ

$ ls -1 applesoft/

$ ls -1 intbasic/
HELLO
APPLESOFT
ANIMALS
COLOR DEMOS
MASTER.CREATE
COPY

$ ls -1 locks/
APPLESOFT
MASTER.CREATE
RAWDOS
COPY
COPY.OBJ

$ touch locks/HELLO
$ ls -1 locks/
HELLO
APPLESOFT
MASTER.CREATE
RAWDOS
COPY
COPY.OBJ

$ cat catalog

DISK VOLUME 254

*I 002 HELLO
*I 043 APPLESOFT
 I 016 ANIMALS
 I 009 COLOR DEMOS
*I 004 MASTER.CREATE
*B 039 RAWDOS
*I 007 COPY
*B 007 COPY.OBJ

$ cat files/HELLO
...BINARY IN OUTPUT...

$ cat intbasic/HELLO
10  PRINT "HI"
20  GOTO 10

$


```